DDTwitter
=========

Abstract
--------

DDTwitter is a tool for twitter.  It has three faces - "background" and
"foreground".

As "background" face, it fetches tweets, direct messages, and other information
that you are interested from the Twitter, then it stores fetched data into
a database which is powered by sqlite.

As "foreground" face, it acts as an abstract interface to read/write from/to
the database for Twitter.

Additionally, a Vim plugin is bundled.  The plugin provides text-based,
comprehensive and useful Twitter client inside Vim.


Requirements
------------

Ruby 1.8.7 or later			<http://www.ruby-lang.org/>
twitter (Ruby gem) 0.6.14 or later	<http://twitter.rubyforge.org/>
sqlite 3.4.0 or later			<http://www.sqlite.org/>

Assumption: Works only on *nix-like environments


Installation
------------

Copy bin/ddtwitter in a package to anywhere you want.


Configuration
-------------

Whenever executing ddtwitter, the directory $HOME/.ddtwitter is created.
Files for DDTwitter is put into the directory

$HOME/.ddtwitter/config
	Some configurations

$HOME/.ddtwitter/database
	Twitter database file.


